## Rules

{% if profile.design_ui.component_library %}
1. Use **{{ profile.design_ui.component_library }}** components as the primary building blocks
2. Do not introduce alternative component libraries
3. Check existing components before creating new ones
{% endif %}

{% if profile.design_ui.css_methodology == 'tailwind' %}
4. Use Tailwind utility classes — avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
5. Extract repeated patterns into components, not utility classes
6. Use the project's Tailwind config for colors, spacing, and typography
{% elif profile.design_ui.css_methodology == 'modules' %}
4. Use CSS Modules for component-scoped styles
5. Follow BEM naming within modules where applicable
{% elif profile.design_ui.css_methodology == 'css-in-js' %}
4. Use the project's CSS-in-JS solution for all component styles
5. Keep styles co-located with their components
{% elif profile.design_ui.css_methodology %}
4. Follow **{{ profile.design_ui.css_methodology }}** patterns consistently
{% endif %}

{% if profile.design_ui.uses_shared_design_system %}
## Shared Design System

{% if profile.design_ui.shared_design_system_name %}
This project uses the **{{ profile.design_ui.shared_design_system_name }}** shared design system.
{% endif %}

- Follow the design system's guidelines for components, tokens, and patterns
- Do not override design system tokens without approval
{% endif %}

